Description: Explore, Connect, Transform
Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Eposak means achievement in the Pemona Kamarakota indigenous language and we are experiential projects of sustainable tourism with impact. We promote and develop projects that foster the growth of unique communities with great tourist potential, and we carry out experiences so that tourists can connect with the impact that these projects generate in tourist destinations. We were born in 2011 as an initiative of the Esteban Torbar Foundation (FET) to create a microfinance platform for tourism entrepreneurs at the base of the pyramid in potentially tourist communities. We submitted our project to the "Geotourism Challenge: Destinations on the Edge" contest, sponsored by National Geographic, the Inter-American Development Bank (IDB) and Ashoka Changemakers and was one of the 7 winners and the only one from Venezuela. Although due to external factors we could not obtain the prize funds, we decided to develop the model on a smaller scale in 5 communities in Venezuela (Kamarata, Birongo, Pueblos del Sur, Mango de Ocoyta and Puerto Sur). Under this scheme we were able to finance and execute more than 40 projects in the aforementioned communities, through an online crowdfunding platform, developed and programmed in-house.   This model mutated as Venezuela changed, until in 2014 we decided to include experiential trips to connect tourists with the communities and instead of supporting entrepreneurial projects, we began to finance more ambitious community projects with a greater impact on the communities. After several years of learning and fine-tuning our project design and selection policy, in 2019 we finally managed to integrate experiential travel into our project execution strategy, which is now described as EXPERIENTIAL PROJECTS that transform lives through sustainable tourism. Our current projects are especially focused on the development of education in unique, remote communities with great tourism potential, and fall into the following categories: culture, sports, technology and environment.

Description: Pinsoft is state-of-the-art software that aids in the efficient management of property & casualty insurance companies.
Headquarters Regions: Midwestern US
Full Description: Pinsoft® is state-of-the-art software that aids in the efficient management of property & casualty insurance companies. Their software includes flexibility in system setup, digital images of risks and claims, drag and drop form assignment and many other intelligent features. They are integrating into their systems many functions that are currently accomplished by small companies off-line on spreadsheets or available only through special report writing. One example is premium loss analysis by agent by policy type. In addition, open access is provided to the vast amount of policy and claim data that is stored by their systems via other third party report writers, such as Crystal Reports, by installing an open database connectivity (ODBC) driver available from SoftVelocity. Their Pinsoft systems interface to the general ledger via ASCII text files. Because of its simplicity and excellent fit with small insurers they recommend use of the Adagio® general ledger from Softrak Systems. Their initial release included policy issuance, claims, and integrated policy rating, integrated reinsurance and integrated check writing. They have now rolled out their agent web access and quoting product which allows agents to view their insured's policy and claim information as well as giving your agents the ability to quote and submit applications via the web. The submitted applications can be imported into Pinsoft with no re-entry of data.  Use of the Internet will encompass additional costs, which have yet to be determined and will be based in part on the Internet service and speed available at your company office.

Description: An e-commerce start-up that makes homebrewing an easy-to-learn and affordable hobby accessible to any college student.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: College Brewer is an e-commerce start-up that makes homebrewing an easy-to-learn and affordable hobby accessible to any college student.  Studies show that 4 out of 5 college students consume beer on a regular basis with the average student drinking 48.3 gallons annually. With over 21 million students currently enrolled in US colleges there is a huge opportunity to introduce homebrewing into an untapped college market.  In 2012, homebrewing generated over $1 billion in annual economic activity, growing at over 20 percent a year. Most of this new growth comes from young adults who are introduced to the DIY brewing craze, yet no one is targeting the enormous beer brazen college market. The perception is that homebrewing is a complicated and expensive hobby. Without any clear direction many would-be brewers are intimidated and give up before they even start. Many that do try homebrewing end up wasting hundreds of dollars on unnecessary equipment, ending up with bad beer. That's a problem…and an opportunity.   That's where College Brewer comes in.  We've simplified homebrewing. Everything has been broken down into the basics so that brewing your own beer is an easy-to-learn and fulfilling hobby. Between our online support, easy to follow instructions, and video database you'll never be stranded without an answer. And not only that, we've made everything affordable. College students are on a budget. Understandable considering they’re entering what is possibly the most debt ridden portion of their life. We’ve developed Brew Kits that allow brewers to make their own beer at college without breaking the bank.  To reach this goal College Brewer is seeking $50,000 in equity investment to fund the business start-up.
Industry Groups: Commerce and Shopping, Food and Beverage

Under the leadership of William Bradford Jr., the Fort Mill Times became a true voice of the people and the paper championed a number of important causes. Using the paper as a bully pulpit, Bradford was credited with getting the state to build a new bridge linking York and Lancaster counties on Doby’s Bridge Road. He crusaded against a poultry processing plant that was unpopular with residents. The plant closed and left town. In 1965, Bradford sold the paper to Tri­County Publishing of Lancaster, a subsidiary of Leroy Springs & Co., the textile firm that was the center of town for more than a century. Bradford remained editor under new publishers Julian Starr Jr. and Paul League. Bradford re­acquired the Fort Mill Times in 1970 and once again served as publisher until 1979, when he sold the paper to the Camden Co. Fred Sheheen, Camden’s owner, became publisher of the Times.
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Food and Beverage, Media and Entertainment

Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: JudicialStats is an information technology company dedicated to providing data on decision-making and increasing judicial transparency.  Put simply, we provide hard data for a soft science: legal risk assessment. The continued growth of litigation is perhaps the simplest proof that a better source of judicial statistics is necessary.  Litigation is expensive and inefficient; generally speaking, it occurs because two parties assess the risks and potential benefits very differently, and cannot come to a fair settlement.  Despite an ongoing information revolution, litigation has steadily increased.  Even sophisticated parties and experienced council have very limited access to hard data depicting decision risks and pendency costs. With JudicialStats, the hard data is finally here.  JudicialStats was founded by attorneys and information company executives with decades of experience in litigation assessment and fiscal and statistical analysis at major law firms and information services companies. All of their expertise is brought to bear on the rich infographic reports available for purchase through JudicialStats.
